The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Briefs

 A 

 mother-daughter duo was detained in Salt Lake for allegedly 

 stealing a diamond ring from a jewellery shop in BE block. 

 An officer of Bidhannagar (north) police station said the 

 woman and her 23-year-old daughter had gone to the shop to 

 buy a wedding ring. 

 Two 

 women and a man were arrested at Azad Hind Nagar in Sodepur, 

 on the northern fringes of the city, on Thursday on charges 

 of rioting. Police said trouble broke out between two local 

 groups over the control of a club. 

 A 

 66-year-old woman died after being knocked down by a private 

 bus at the crossing of Surahwardy Avenue and Darga Road, in 

 Beniapukur, on Wednesday night. The vehicle was impounded 

 and the driver arrested. 

 One 

 person was killed and two others were injured on Thursday 

 evening when the Chennai-Howrah Mail knocked them down at 

 Kulgachhia, in Howrah. 

 Power 

 supply will be disrupted in the Gangarampur, Chatta, Subid 

 Ali Road and Mahesh Gote areas between 10 am and 4 pm on Friday 

 owing to maintenance work by the CESC. 




